hopobject.body: Where's the postbox? celadrin webmd It is rare for any opponent to out-serve Federer or to hit more winners but the statistics in Murray's four-hour victory told their own story. The Scot has probably never served so consistently well. He hit 21 aces to Federer's five thanks to a combination of power and clever variations of spin and placement. Federer repeatedly struggled to hold serve, while Murray's tally of winners (62 to Federer's 43) and unforced errors (47 against 60) were testament to his domination.
